e the computational bubble is actually\nsteady and its oscillations are represented purely with time-dependent boundary\nconditions. A numerical comparison with the moving domain model confirms that\nthis simplification is perfectly reasonable for the class of problems\ninvestigated in this paper.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 Jun 2022 10:48:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-25"}
